A.B Umar, a lecturer who was sacked from Ahmadu Bello University Zaria for sexually harassing a female studenthas been allegedly reemployed by Kaduna state University. A Twitter user expressed his disappoinment about this. The tweet caught the attention of Kaduna state Governor, Nasir El-Rufai, who has vowed to immediately investigate the matter and see to the sack of the Lecturer if true. See his tweet below: SHOCKED!!: Thanks for drawing our attention to this. The Commssioner of Education and Attorney-General of Kaduna State will jointly commence investigation of this right away and take further action. Our Deputy Governor @DrHadiza will monitor to closure. @MuyiwaAdekeye @Dattijo https://t.co/1pfrkGCrBG